
CSS Box Model & Layout
Today's Focus: Margin, Padding, Border, and Display Properties
What I Learned:

Box Model: content, padding, border, margin

display property: block, inline, inline-block

Centering elements: margin: 0 auto

Border styles and radius

Practice Exercise: Create profile cards

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        .card {
            width: 300px;
            border: 2px solid #3498db;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            text-align: center;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        .profile-img {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            border: 3px solid #2ecc71;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background: #3498db;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="card">
        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/100" class="profile-img" alt="Profile">
        <h2>John Doe</h2>
        <p>Full Stack Developer</p>
        <p>Learning HTML, CSS, JavaScript</p>
        <a href="#" class="btn">View Profile</a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

